I installed Yaary after seeing their ads claiming to be India's first driver-focused mobility app. I was hoping to find a cheap and convenient ride-hailing service in Hyderabad. But I was very disappointed by how expensive and unreliable Yaary was. I tried to book a ride with Yaary from my office to home, which is only 4.5 km away. The app showed me a fare of Rs 200, which is 40% more than what other apps charge for the same distance. I thought it was a mistake, so I refreshed the app and tried
